When making changes:
1. Keep knowledge-base/ updated with every implementation change
2. Evaluate against Elite Benchmarks — reject changes that don't improve Sharpe/PF
3. Every trading rule must be mathematically defined (no subjective interpretation)
4. Risk first — discuss MAE and Sharpe before discussing profits
5. DO NOT optimize core parameters (WMA, SMMA, swing lookback)
6. Test with: py -m pytest tests/ -v --tb=short
